{
  "text": "Arbitrary multi-beam MSRAs can be synthesized designing the modulated surface reactance as the interference pattern between the surface wave ( ) excited by the feed and the superposition of the fields required at the surface to create each far field beams ( , ), i.e. the steering vectors to the desired angles [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the required surface impedance can be expressed as [CITATION_2] ",
